# LAMMPS Input File
# Licensed under CC BY 4.0
# A Set of Materials-Science Tutorials for the LAMMPS Simulation Package
# Tutorial 14: chemical short-range order in a high-entropy alloy
#
# Same hybrid MD/MC protocol as sro-hot.lmp (1300 K), but with the
# seven-element 2NN-MEAM potential of Wang et al., npj Comput. Mater. 9, 60
# (2023) (bundled with LAMMPS), restricted to the four CoCrFeNi elements.
# Its positive Cr-Fe and Co-Cr mixing enthalpies (see mixing-2nnmeam.lmp)
# expel chromium from the solid solution: instead of developing short-range
# order, the alloy phase-separates into a Cr precipitate.

units metal
atom_style atomic
boundary p p p

variable T equal 1300.0

# 1) build a random equimolar CoCrFeNi crystal (fcc, 5x5x5 = 500 atoms)
lattice fcc 3.56
region box block 0 5 0 5 0 5
create_box 4 box
create_atoms 1 box
# randomly assign exactly one quarter of the sites to each element
set group all type/subset 2 125 12345
set type 1   type/subset 3 125 23456
set type 1   type/subset 4 125 34567
mass 1 58.933   # Co
mass 2 51.996   # Cr
mass 3 55.845   # Fe
mass 4 58.693   # Ni
pair_style meam
pair_coeff * * library_2nn.meam Mo Co Ni V Fe Al Cr MoCoNiVFeAlCr_2nn.meam Co Cr Fe Ni

variable peat equal pe/count(all)

# 2) thermalize the atomic positions at temperature T (no swaps yet)
velocity all create ${T} 9988 mom yes rot yes dist gaussian
fix md all npt temp ${T} ${T} 0.1 iso 0.0 0.0 1.0
thermo 500
thermo_style custom step temp pe press
run 2000
write_dump all custom random-2nnmeam.dump id type x y z modify sort id

# 3) hybrid MD/MC: every 40 MD steps attempt 40 identity swaps for each
#    element pair, accepted with the Metropolis criterion at temperature T
fix s12 all atom/swap 40 40 701 ${T} types 1 2
fix s13 all atom/swap 40 40 702 ${T} types 1 3
fix s14 all atom/swap 40 40 703 ${T} types 1 4
fix s23 all atom/swap 40 40 704 ${T} types 2 3
fix s24 all atom/swap 40 40 705 ${T} types 2 4
fix s34 all atom/swap 40 40 706 ${T} types 3 4
fix peout all ave/time 100 1 100 v_peat file energy-2nnmeam.dat
dump traj all custom 500 anneal-2nnmeam.dump id type x y z
dump_modify traj sort id
run 12000
write_dump all custom ordered-2nnmeam.dump id type x y z modify sort id
write_data ordered-2nnmeam.data
